Hi Daniel, 

 

We know inboxes get busy, so heres a quick recap of the most popular courses launched this year so far at DeepLearning.AI.

 

These courses have been among the most enrolled by our community, and they cover practical skills across AI agents, RAG, vibe coding, and more:

    MCP: Build Rich-Context AI Apps with Anthropic

    In this hands-on course built in collaboration with Anthropic, youll learn how to use the Model Context Protocol (MCP) to simplify the way AI applications connect to external systems like GitHub, Google Docs, or web content. Youll build an MCP-compatible chatbot, deploy an MCP server, and explore how this open protocol streamlines tool and data integration across LLM-based apps like Claude Desktop, making AI development more scalable and less fragmented.

      Enroll for Free

      Building with Llama 4

      Learn to build powerful, multimodal applications with Llama 4 in this hands-on course made in collaboration with Meta. Taught by Amit Sangani, Director of Partner Engineering at Meta, the course explores Llama 4s Mixture-of-Experts architecture, long-context capabilities, and two of their three new models: Maverick and Scout. Youll experiment with image grounding, multi-image reasoning, and massive text inputs using the official Llama API and Together.ai. Youll also try out Metas prompt optimization tool and synthetic data kit to improve and fine-tune your applications.

        Enroll for Free

        Vibe Coding 101 with Replit

        Build real apps with the help of an AI coding agent. Learn how to collaborate with coding agents to prototype, debug, and deploy applications in Replits cloud environment. In this hands-on course created with Replit, youll build a website performance analyzer and a head-to-head voting app while strengthening your development skills through structured prompting, effective debugging, and agentic coding principles that help you vibe code with clarity and intention.

         

        Enroll for Free

        How Transformer LLMs Work

        Understand the architecture behind todays most powerful LLMs. This course, created with the authors of the Hands-On Large Language Models book, breaks down how transformer models work, covering tokenization, embeddings, attention mechanisms, and recent transformer optimizations like KV caching and grouped query attention. You'll build a strong technical foundation, explore the Hugging Face Transformers library, and gain the intuition to understand model architecture and build more effective LLM applications.

          Enroll for Free

          Bonus! Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG)

          Yesterday, we launched this hands-on course where youll learn how to design, build, and evaluate production-ready RAG pipelines, from retrieval strategies and vector databases to prompt engineering and system deployment. Youll explore key tradeoffs, tackle real-world challenges like latency and context limits, and work with tools like Weaviate and Arize Phoenix across domains like e-commerce and healthcare. By the end, youll be equipped to create grounded, accurate AI applications that go beyond the proof of concept.

            Enroll Now
